sec.p:
We built correlations among 29 clinical phenomes based on the common genes/proteins between two traits. To minimize the bias in estimating the correlation between two given traits, we calculated the molecular comorbidity index (MCI) by adapting the formula from Grosdidier S [67] to further consider the different coefficients of distance between the two diseases. The MCI was defined as follows:
